      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I understand your intention to stay authentic, but it's important to recognize that urban streetwear is deeply rooted in the experiences and cultures of marginalized communities, particularly African American and Latino youth. Appropriating elements without understanding or respecting their significance can be harmful. Instead, focus on collaborating with individuals from those communities, and let their voices guide your designs. This way, you can capture the essence of urban streetwear while honoring its origins.",
